main event: On April 3, 1966, a round object was observed hovering and moving overhead in Waukesha, Wisconsin for approximately 5 minutes.
interesting points: The object was described as being the size of a baseball and bright orange in color., Observers noted that the object had an antenna sticking out of the top., The object was first spotted at about 2 miles in the air and flew directly above the observers' car., The car failed to start while the object was overhead but started again once it dimmed., There was a young person present who was unable to describe the object.
sighted object: round bright orange object with an antenna
witness description: Civilians, including a young person who did not describe the object
